## Research

I use math models to study the ecology and evolution of infectious diseases. Infectious diseases occur often occur across multiple scales. For instance, in epidemics models there is the individual level, where transmission is often quantified by the reproduction number, "R0" and the population level, where transmission is quantifed by the observed exponential growth rate of new cases, "r"

 studied heterogeneity of cell responses in flu infections. 
 

